- Therefore: g(y) = (f(x₀+y) + f(x₀-y))/(2f(x₀))
- Using |f| ≤ 1 and the triangle inequality: |g(y)| ≤ (|f(x₀+y)| + |f(x₀-y)|)/(2|f(x₀)|) ≤ 2/(2|f(x₀)|) = 1/|f(x₀)|

